OL,3,CMan defrauded elderly mum of more than
OL,4,C#100,000 to pay own bills
OL,6,FA man who defrauded his elderly mother
OL,7,Fout of more than #100,000 to pay his
OL,8,Fown bills has avoided an immediate
OL,9,Fprison sentence.
OL,11,FRobert Catlow, from Todmorden, took
OL,12,F#112,000 from his mother over a five-
OL,13,Fyear period while she was being looked
OL,14,Fafter in a care home in West Yorkshire.
OL,16,FThe 54-year-old, who was living in his
OL,17,Fparents' home at the time and had
OL,18,Fpower of attorney, used the money to
OL,19,Ffund his own business and pay his
OL,20,Fhousehold bills.
